Mezzo, a programming language with permissions
----------------------------------------------


            http://gallium.inria.fr/~protzenk/mezzo-lang


In order to compile, Mezzo requires:
- OCaml 4.00
- a properly-working ocamlfind command,
- the following packages: menhir, yojson, ulex, pprint, functory, fix

These packages are present in Debian but Debian hasn't switched to OCaml 4.00
yet. We recommend OPAM <http://opam.ocamlpro.com> to easily install
these dependencies.


Compiling
---------

make


Running Mezzo
-------------

./mezzo --help


Running tests
-------------

make test
